{"id": "1505718483286102139", "channel_id": "1505686711403806812", "author_id": "231543819026300928", "author_name": "crowlov1", "content": "Nah the core part is fine. They even talked about it a while back in Arle interview. But they just overshot the cost for these changes.\n\nThey added the 10% buff to limited units back then to incentivize people to use limited units. To make them more juicy.\n\nEphemeral part.... Yeah I got nothing I agree with you here.", "timestamp": "2026-05-17T23:47:41.312000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1505686711403806812", "mentions": ["277927692735873035"], "reply_to": "1505710591908778035"}
{"id": "1505720883296337921", "channel_id": "1505686711403806812", "author_id": "277927692735873035", "author_name": "choco_minnto", "content": "either way it’s poorly executed \n\nlight said giving dev logs in advance would be mandatory ever since his last apology, which didn’t happen. \n\nhad he done that, he would have received player feedback and could have made better changes, instead of causing the riot we have now \n\nalso, isn’t it the opposite? most standard units aren’t viable in end game content (alert 5 / arc 2 hard mode) and most players use standard units as supports to their limited awakener carries\n\nwhy does biav need to incentivise people to use limited units when standard units sees less use? \n\nshouldn’t they be giving the 10% stat buff to incentivise more viable standard teams instead of meta spam with limited units ?", "timestamp": "2026-05-17T23:57:13.519000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1505686711403806812", "mentions": ["231543819026300928"], "reply_to": "1505718483286102139"}
